The Office of the Public Protector should get its house in order, as continuous scandals surrounding Busisiwe Mkhwebane could tarnish the integrity of the institution and that of all chapter 9 institutions, analysts say. Mkhwebane is at the centre of a number of dramas, including a process before parliament to remove her from office, a criminal investigation by the Hawks, as well as the South African Revenue Service (Sars) probing her income tax affairs. Her credibility has been in question since some of her findings have been overturned in the courts. At a media briefing on Tuesday, where she gave...